race.comment: HUBBLE'S DRAGON (4) was very impressive from the front first-up on the Scarpside at Pinjarra, kicking away to win comfortably over 1200m. He'll be better for that effort and the form out of that race has worked out well. Pike sticks, he can roll across from out wide and he can bring up back-to-back wins. BULLETIN BEAU (1) missed by 0.6L fresh before winning in a photo over 1200m at Pinjarra last time out. Has the speed to roll across from out wide and third-up into the campaign can see him at his best. Building nicely and can raise the bar again. GOD'S CROSS (3) showed good improvement over this trip on the Scarpside to score comfortably from a midfield position. Drawn nicely today and can repeat the dose in a race that looks to set up nicely for him. I'M GENEVIEVE (11) can improve on the first-up effort where she stuck on well in Saturday grade. ALMA MATER (5) can be in the finish first-up.
